\begin{remark}
We point out that the hypothesis $\phi\in L^q(\Omega)$ {\it is not needed} in Theorem \ref{thm:mother}. Rather, inequality \eqref{filippica} permits to show that on a convex set, functions in $\ddot{\mathrm{W}}^{1,p}_{q-1}(\Omega)$ and with finite moment of order $p/(p-q)$ are automatically in $L^q(\Omega)$.
\end{remark}

